<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TimeML><TIMEX3 tid="t0" functionInDocument="CREATION_TIME"/>Italian Marco Saligari <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">won</EVENT> the sixth stage  of the Tour of Italy here on <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE">Friday</TIMEX3> after a 210km five-man breakaway.&#13;
Saligari's triumph, just over three minutes ahead of the peleton <EVENT eid="e2" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">following</EVENT>  a sprint to the line, gave him an unusual hat-trick, <EVENT eid="e3" class="I_ACTION" tense="PRESPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">allowing</EVENT> him to <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="INFINITIVE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">record</EVENT> a  stage <EVENT eid="e5" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">win</EVENT> for the third Giro running.&#13;
Overall leader Evgeni Berzin of Russia <EVENT eid="e6" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">retained</EVENT> the pink jersey at the end  of the 215km run.&#13;
The <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DURATION">29-year-old</TIMEX3> Italian winner, who <EVENT eid="e7" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">won</EVENT> <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DATE">last year</TIMEX3>'s Tour of Switzerland,  <EVENT eid="e8" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">stole</EVENT> away from the pack with fellow Italians Massimo Ghirotto, Ivan Gotti and  Gianni Faresin, as well as Heinz Imboden of Switzerland. Ghirotto <EVENT eid="e9" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">came</EVENT> home in  second.&#13;
